      "writtenOn": "2016-11-08T15:54:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: \"s\" is a bit loaded when it comes to color configs (srgb, etc.). And \"int\" could potentially be unclear on whether it refers to the storage format or the fact that it represents non-unorm. Do you think \"kRGBA_8888_integer\" would be less or more ambiguous?",
