      "writtenOn": "2016-11-09T15:22:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027re right, there really isn\u0027t confusion about what \"sint\" means. I guess it\u0027s just not a common abbreviation for \"signed integer\".\n\n\u003e\u003e but then what will we call unsigned integer formats\n\nI suppose just \"_unsigned_\" could work too, like in C.\n\nThis isn\u0027t a big deal. \"_sint_\"/\"_uint_\"/\"_integer_\"/\"_unsigned_\" are all fine with me.",
      "parentUuid": "2bde5729_6b45808b",
